<h1>Case 2 — Smart Governance & Citizen Service Centre</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Smart Governance & Citizen Service Centre acts as a unified digital hub for citizens 
to access services such as certificate requests, grievance filing, bill payments, document management, 
and verification. It ensures transparency, reduces waiting time, and improves government efficiency.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Long queues in physical government offices causing delays.</li>
    <li>Mismanagement or loss of important citizen documents.</li>
    <li>Difficulty in routing grievances to the correct department.</li>
    <li>No priority handling for senior citizens, emergencies, or disability cases.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> For instant citizen record lookup and document indexing.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Managing citizen service requests and token-based flow.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Handling high-priority cases such as medical or senior-citizen requests first.</li>
    <li><strong>Trie / Search Optimization:</strong> Fast search of documents, names, and service types.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 16 — Peace, Justice & Strong Institutions</strong>
    <p>Ensures transparent, accountable, and efficient public service delivery.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Promotes digital transformation and smart governance technologies.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 10 — Reduced Inequalities</strong>
    <p>Provides equal access to citizen services with priority for vulnerable groups.</p>
</div>

